	<div id="content" class="hfeed">
	<article class="post-26067 post type-post status-publish hentry category-artsbeat category-books tag-frank-mccourt" id="post-26067">
	<header class="postHeader">
				<div class="postKicker">
					</div>
				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Share Your Memories of Frank McCourt</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By The New York Times			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2009-07-20T01:34:25+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">July 19, 2009 9:34 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">July 19, 2009 9:34 pm</span>		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div class="w75 left"><img src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2009/07/20/obituaries/20mccourt.752.jpg" /></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Frank McCourt, a former New York City schoolteacher who turned his childhood in Limerick, Ireland, into a phenomenally popular, Pulitzer Prize-winning memoir, “Angela’s Ashes,” <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2009/07/20/books/20mccourt.html">died in Manhattan on Sunday</a>. He was 78 and lived in Manhattan and Roxbury, Conn. </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Mr. McCourt spent three decades as a teacher of English and creative writing in New York City’s public schools. As <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2009/07/20/books/20frank.html">Eric Konigsberg writes</a>, Mr. McCourt was the first to say that &#8220;those years, while depriving him of the time to actually write, were what made a writer out of him.&#8221;  And his students learned from him that &#8220;literature was nothing more — and nothing less — than the telling of stories.&#8221;</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Were you a student of Mr. McCourt&#8217;s? Or a fan of his work? <a href="//artsbeat.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/07/19/share-your-memories-of-frank-mccourt/#respond">Share your memories</a> of the teacher-turned-Pulitzer Prize-winning author. </p>
	</div>
		<footer class="entry-footer">
					<div id="sharetools-post-footer" class="sharetools theme-classic" data-shares="show-all|Share" data-url="//artsbeat.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/07/19/share-your-memories-of-frank-mccourt/" data-title="Share Your Memories of Frank McCourt" data-description="Were you a student of Mr. McCourt&#039;s? Or a fan of his work? Share your memories of the teacher-turned-Pulitzer Prize-winning author. ">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad hidden"></div>
			</div>		<div class="footer-tags">
					</div>
		</footer>
</article>
