				</a>
			</span>
		</div>
		<div class="comment-content" style="display:block;">

			<p>I still remember the first day of English Class, and the only time Mr. McCourt assigned us a book to read  for the entire term. &#8220;You will read, Thomas Wolfe&#8217;s &#8216;You Can&#8217;t Go Home Again&#8217;, he had said in a melodic accent that I, a sheltered, first generation Asian-American, found so refreshing from the harsh Queens accent I often heard on the 45-minute subway commute to Stuyvesant HS. Class was 40 minutes of storytelling by this wonderfully gifted and engaging author, and I was encouraged to write from my own voice as a child of immigrant parents. Although my creative writing is now mostly kept in my journals for personal reading, Mr. McCourt left me with the legacy and appreciation of family, and the desire to go out into the world and seek the experiences that create memories . He will be missed.</p>

		</div>
	</div><!-- #comment-## -->
