			<p>I had the great honor to meet Frank McCourt when he came to San Francisco several years ago to do a reading from &#8220;Teacher Man&#8221; on a local radio show. As charmed as I was by his lilting Irish brogue, I must admit that his dry wit is what I will remember most. Approaching him after the show as he was preparing to autograph books, I mentioned pensively that I had all of his books at home, but had forgotten to bring them with me, to which he instantly replied (his blue eyes flashing), &#8220;Well, let me come home with you then!&#8221;  </p>
<p>&#8216;Twill be a long time before we see the likes of that kind of literary talent again.  May you be &#8220;halfway to Heaven before the devil knows you&#8217;re gone&#8221;, Frank.</p>

