			<p>I was privileged to have Frank McCourt as my creative writing teacher at Stuyvesant.  Every day he taught us to think for ourselves, from our own experiences.  He taught us the magic of language and the poetry of everyday existence.  I was blessed to have his encouragement to start an underground newspaper when our school paper was censored, and will never forget going over galleys at the White Horse or Lion&#8217;s Head.  Rest in peace Mr. McCourt, you will be well missed and deeply remembered.</p>

